15/08/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Army chief General Nikola Kolev announced on Friday (12 August) that the military command had decided to cancel two planned drills in the aftermath of recent heavy flooding.
Kolev said that the army cancelled the national exercise "Autumn 2005" and would re-allocate resources to flooded regions.
He also has requested that Romania agree to postpone a planned bilateral drill in the Black Sea.
(Mediapool, BNR, Trud - 13/08/05)
